                Security and Visitors Management System

1. Identifying a Real-World Problem 

•	The Issue: Right now, security guards have to manually write down everything in gate logs.
•	The Observation: I noticed they even write down school bus departure times by hand whenever they take students out.
•	The Impact: These manual logs are hard to search, easy to mess up, and don't give any real-time info on whether a bus or visitor is still on site.

2. Finding the "Gap" 

•	The Gap: The school already has a system to check students in and out, but it completely ignores visitors, staff, and the bus fleet.
•	Our Innovation: We can bridge this gap by creating a unified portal that handles what the current system cannot.

3. What the System Will Do

•	Visitor Management: Digital registration for guests with entry/exit timestamps.
•	Bus Dispatch Module: A simple way for guards to log bus plate numbers and departure times with one click.
•	Smart Alerts: The system flags the supervisor if a bus hasn't returned or a visitor hasn't checked out on time.

/Things we need to add in the System

1.	Reason for visit – for example 10 admissions, inquires etc.
2.	Why has a visitor overstayed e.g. like 5 hours?
3.	Replace Total Records with Total Entries.
4.  Automate the ID so that it’s unique to everyone instead of typing.
5.	Include a graph to show statistics on the dashboard.
6.	System admin, should create accounts

